post_text: Congratulations to GVHS for ranking first in the statewide high school division and top ten in the Statewide All Divisions spring 2020 competition of the PA Council on Financial Literacy's Stock Market Challenge! The winning student for both was Jack Stapf under the guidance of teacher Kurt Balderson. Teams of students each managed a hypothetical investment of $100,000 in stocks, bonds, and mutual funds and made buying and trading decisions based on the stock market. The students who traded and finished the competition with the most money won.

GVMS students performed very well on the first administration of the National Latin Exam at the middle school! For the Introduction to Latin Exam, Camille Derval, Pranay Thatikonda, Isabella Acker, and Nishtha Gupta all earned Certificates of Achievement. For the Latin I Exam,
Dante Stefanelli and Riya Naguluri earned Cum Laude honors; Grant Bardsley and Dane Teter earned Magna Cum Laude honors. Congratulations to our students!

post_text: Three Great Valley High School students (Riya Kinny, Prithvi Parthasarathy and Kyle Yang) participated in The West Point Society of Philadelphia's 2020 Leadership and Ethics Conference at Villanova University in early March. Held in partnership with the university, The Travis Manion Foundation, and local college ROTC departments, the conference explored ethical issues of honor, respect and leadership. GVHS teacher Mr. Ellis accompanied the students.

post_text: Five Great Valley Middle School students recently earned distinction in the American Mathematics Competition. The AMC 8 is a 25-question, 40-minute, multiple choice test designed to promote the development of problem-solving skills. Students apply classroom skills to unique problem-solving challenges. The material covered includes topics from a typical middle school mathematics curriculum. Congratulations to: Ethan Zhou, Bronze Award; Patrick Li, Silver Award; Yash Pandya, Bronze Award; Owen Li, Gold Award (high score for GVMS and in the top 5% in the country); and Angelina Wang, Certificate of Achievement.

Quite a remarkable and memorable day for Great Valley students in the Big Apple!

post_text: The Great Valley High School Drama Guild will present "The 39 Steps." Performances are November 22 and 23. Evening performances are at 7:30 p.m. on both nights, with a matinee at 2:00 p.m. on November 23. Ticket prices are $15 for adults and $10 for students/seniors 65 years and over. Seniors 65 years and over are free for the Saturday matinee performance. Performances will be held at Great Valley High School. For additional information and tickets, please visit the Drama Guild's online ticketing page at https://app.arts-people.com/index.php?ticketing=gvdg.

Two upcoming ‚Äúworkshops,‚Äù will engage the community in conversations to consider not only facility needs, but also the allocation of resources, and possible building renovations, improvements, additions/closings, and grade reconfigurations. This process will culminate in a comprehensive master plan for the District to follow for the next five to ten years. Learn more and register to attend at www.gvsd.org/facilitymeetings
